<Author>SlaviaPraha
<Content>Lousy Hotel We have recently stayed at this hotel and found the whole experience horrible, and certainly the worst value for money we have had for many years.The staff were unfriendly to the point of being ignorant. They were also extremely unhelpful. We are senior citizens and had to find our own way to our room, carrying our luggage first up a flight of stairs from reception to a lift which went down to a courtyard. We had to go up three floors, leave the lift, go down a flight of stairs and along a corridor to our room.The room was facing the courtyard which afforded no privacy at all when using the bathroom. We were also asked not to put toilet paper down the toilet, which we found to be a disgusting request. At night there were generators continually buzzing in the courtyard making sleep difficult.Perhaps the worst experience was that staff entered our room when we were out during the evening and left the door open, fortunately nothing was stolen.Breakfast was from 7am to 10am. If you are down in the breakfast room later than 8am most of the buffet was gone, and was not replenished.The hotel does not have a bar.All in all, I cannot advise that you stay in this hotel. There are many better value hotles in Berlin. 
