<Author>michiganmarlon
<Content>Sehr gut! I very much enjoyed my may 19-22 stay at the Hotel Augusta, a charming small hotel in a superb location right off the Ku'Damm in exciting Berlin.The hotel is on Fasanenstrasse, a relatively quiet, fashionable street less than a half block from the commercial carnival that is the Kurfurstendamm. The hotel has a small charming lobby a flight of stairs up from its entrance. The rooms are cozy, well-decorated, bright and very comfortable. Bathrooms are compact but more than adequate, with glassed in showers. The beds were very comfortable, and the courtyard rooms - which we had - were very quiet.The breakfast room was bright and cheerful, with a very good breakfast buffet that included plenty of croissants, danishes, fruit, cold cuts, eggs, cheeses, good coffee, tea and juices.The location is great - right off the Ku'Damm and a half-block from the Uhlandstrasse U-bahn station. If you're taking bus 109 from Tegel Airport, just get off at Uhlandstrasse and walk around the corner. The Kaiser Wilhelm Church, Zoo Bahnhof train station, the KaDeWe department store and the broken chains statue are a very short walk away. Berlin's other great attractions can be quickly accessed by the excellent public transportation network. 
