<Author>Richwyl50
<Content>Great Hotel, Great Location The previous review refers to another Hotel Augusta. This one is a charming gem of a hotel. It is completely renovated featuring small but charming and comfortable rooms. I asked for a quiet room and was given one on the Hof, or courtyard, which is filled with plants and trees. The hotel staff were excellent and extremely helpful. Breakfast is served in two sumptuous rooms, one with a balcony overlooking Fasanenstrasse. The location is perfect for Berlin West, right on the Kudamm. I got a great room rate from Berlin Tourismus-Marketing when the hotel I had been staying out turned out to have construction on all sides. I look forward to being able to stay at this hotel again. 
